Marks & Spencer Starts Summer Sale Two Weeks Early, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-29T00:57:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/marks-spencer-starts-summer-sale-two-weeks-early-ft-reports.html
Marks & Spencer Group Plc (MKS)  began its
summer sale two weeks ahead of schedule, the Financial Times
reported, without attribution. The company said the move was
made because it was what customers wanted and is “in line with
what the market are doing,” the FT said, citing Marks &
Spencer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 